# Honcho memory (Cursor)

You have persistent memory via [Honcho](https://honcho.dev). Context about the user, their preferences, and past work may be loaded automatically at session start.

## How to use it

- Trust Honcho context injected at session start when present. Act on it; do not ignore it or ask for things already recorded.
- Use the Honcho MCP tools `chat` or `search` when you need context beyond what was loaded at startup.
- Use `create_conclusion` to save new insights as you learn them (preferences, decisions, patterns, things to avoid).
- The user should not have to repeat stable facts you have already stored.

## Cross-tool setup

If the user also uses Claude Code, they can link `cursor` and `claude_code` workspaces in `~/.honcho/config.json` under `hosts.*.linkedHosts` so context can flow between tools. See the plugin README.
